  • Classes

  • Interfaces 
    Interface Description
    com.amazon.ion.IonBinaryWriter
    Use IonSystem.newBinaryWriter(OutputStream, SymbolTable...) instead.
    com.amazon.ion.IonTextReader
    Use TextSpan instead.
    com.amazon.ion.RawValueSpanProvider
    This is a private API subject to change without notice.
  • Classes 
    Class Description
    com.amazon.ion.system.SystemFactory
    Use the more configurable IonSystemBuilder instead.
  • Exceptions 
    Exceptions Description
    com.amazon.ion.EmptySymbolException
    this exception is not used as empty symbols are valid. In cases where null is used as the symbol value it was replaced by NullPointerException
  • Methods 
    Method Description
    com.amazon.ion.IonBinaryWriter.byteSize()
    com.amazon.ion.IonBinaryWriter.getBytes()
    com.amazon.ion.IonBinaryWriter.writeBytes​(OutputStream)
    com.amazon.ion.IonDatagram.getBytes​(byte[])
    com.amazon.ion.IonDatagram.toBytes()
    Use IonDatagram.getBytes() instead, which is renamed for consistency with other interfaces.
    com.amazon.ion.IonLoader.load​(InputStream)
    Will cause a memory leak when reading a gzipped stream. Use IonLoader.load(IonReader) instead.
    com.amazon.ion.IonReader.getFieldId()
    Use IonReader.getFieldNameSymbol() instead.
    com.amazon.ion.IonReader.hasNext()
    Applications should detect the end of the current level by checking for a null response from IonReader.next().
    com.amazon.ion.IonSymbol.getSymbolId()
    Use IonSymbol.symbolValue() instead.
    com.amazon.ion.IonSystem.iterate​(InputStream)
    Will cause a memory leak when reading a gzipped stream. Use IonSystem.iterate(IonReader) instead.
    com.amazon.ion.IonSystem.newBinaryWriter()
    Use IonSystem.newBinaryWriter(OutputStream, SymbolTable...) instead.
    com.amazon.ion.IonValue.getFieldId()
    Use IonValue.getFieldNameSymbol() instead.
    com.amazon.ion.IonWriter.writeTimestampUTC​(Date)
    Use IonWriter.writeTimestamp(Timestamp.forDateZ(Date)) instead.
    com.amazon.ion.IonWriter.writeValue​(IonValue)
    Use IonValue.writeTo(IonWriter) instead.
    com.amazon.ion.system.SystemFactory.newSystem()
    Use IonSystemBuilder.standard().build() instead.
    com.amazon.ion.Timestamp.createFromUtcFields​(Timestamp.Precision, int, int, int, int, int, int, BigDecimal, Integer)
    com.amazon.ion.Timestamp.getFractionalSecond()
    com.amazon.ion.Timestamp.getZFractionalSecond()
    Use Timestamp.getZDecimalSecond() instead.
    com.amazon.ion.ValueFactory.newList​(Collection<? extends IonValue>)
    This method can be invoked (accidentally and incorrectly) with an IonSequence! Use either ValueFactory.newList(IonValue...) or newList().addAll(Collection).
    com.amazon.ion.ValueFactory.newSexp​(Collection<? extends IonValue>)
    This method can be invoked (accidentally and incorrectly) with an IonSequence! Use either ValueFactory.newSexp(IonValue...) or newSexp().addAll(Collection).
  • Constructors 
    Constructor Description
    com.amazon.ion.Timestamp​(int, int, int)
    Use Timestamp.forDay(int, int, int) instead.

    Enum Constant Description
    com.amazon.ion.Timestamp.Precision.FRACTION
